snippet.textDisplay: First of all, Hats off to Shiraz Uppal for such an amazing composition. Folk we need to understand that every singer is unique in his or her own way as they have a unique vocal texture. Coke Studio is an fine example which brings out the best in everyone (singers, musicians), in this song i loved the amazing sync and collaboration of each other which made this song amazing. Also we also need to mention the amazing singers who accompanied the harmonies and chorus, they have been equally amazing loved it. !! So Please stop hatred and Enjoy the music from your soul. Every country has amazing singer , composers, musicians. Music is the only element which have connected us and will always stay with us forever .

snippet.textDisplay: The 'light' song of the episode. Absolutely loved the singing from both, still conflicted as to who did it better! The arrangement killed the song for me though. With such talented duo on the microphone, a lighter arrangement would have given much more real estate to the singers, sadly it wasn't to be. That said, you will surely not skip the song when it comes up on the playlist on a long drive. Happy vibe,  Excellent tune, could have been so much better though! Why is everyone trying so hard in arranging this
